group_instance_suffix(25.10)                      group_instance_suffix(25.10)

Name
       group_instance_suffix

Syntax
        group_instance_suffix suffix

       Type: String

       Default: i

       This  suffix is added to a new hinst name created by the group command.
       So, group -name abc creates a new module named abc,  and  a  new  hinst
       named  abci.   If you do not want any suffix, you need to set the value
       to the empty string "".

Related Information
              * group

